fields.name: single-link-list-stack
fields.description: A stack is an abstract data structure that follows a LIFO (Last In, First Out) order. This implementation makes use of a singly linked list where each node carries data as well as a pointer to the next node in the list.

fields.name: single-link-list-queue
fields.description: A queue is an abstract data structure that follows a FIFO (First In, First Out) order. This implementation makes use of a singly linked list where each node carries data as well as a pointer to the next node in the list.
